POST_TEXT:
This is a very late post to talk about some highlights from DMEXCO - Digital Marketing Expo & Conference, a huge event in Cologne that I had the opportunity to visit in September, attending (the gorgeous 😍) Channable stand:

😌 Claire Valoti, VP of Snap, said that 82% of Gen Z prefer brands that use images of real customers in advertising. So, real people, we are rejecting this "perfect imaginary" (it's about time);

🤖 She also showed how shopping is becoming more about the person, and not about the product, and how AR is facilitating that (you can "try on" virtually your sneakers, change the color of your nails, and so on), to make sure we can create a sustainable experience for costumers but also for the planet;

🏋 Chris Babayode, Managing Director EMEA at MMA, showed the Modern Marketing Capability map, with 18 areas and 72 areas of expertise for me and my fellow marketers to work on.

🙃 Caroline Hugonenc, SVP Research & Insights at Teads.com, preached for the user's freedom, saying that forced ads require 2x more time to deliver the same impact; 

🗒️ Jens-Christian Jensen, CSO, Digitas Pixelpark, brought the CMO agenda for 2023, with item 4 (Empower your talents and let them make decisions) resonating strongly with me;

🏆 And lastly, but not less important, Alina Kuhnert's presentation "Don't panic with complex product data" was the talk of the day, with lots of practical insights! Looking forward to having it in English as well to share here.

